The gripping drama series, which made its debut in February tells the story of how the lives of three families are torn apart by unfortunate events. Xolile who took a short break to further her studies and spen some time behind the camera is happy to be back in action. You know this role that I m playing teaches a lot of thing, I m playing the character of Angela Ndamase the wife that is wealthy but there s no happiness at home," she told Drum magazine.Xolile added that she was enjoying the reception of her character on the show. People see me in malls and they recognize me as Angela from the show. That s testament that the show is doing well," she added. A post shared by Ingozi (@ingozisabc1) on Jan 27, 2017 at 2:52am PST 